data.title: Enrollment open for K12-powered virtual public schools in Indiana with state-certified teachers.
data.description: Families in Indiana have the opportunity to enroll in full-time virtual public schools that are powered by K12 and led by state-certified teachers. This option allows families to choose a virtual learning environment for their children, ensuring they receive instruction from qualified educators. The virtual public schools offer a comprehensive curriculum and support services to students, providing a quality educational experience. Families interested in enrolling can get more information and begin the process by contacting the school directly. This initiative provides families with the flexibility to access education in a virtual setting, offering an alternative to traditional brick-and-mortar schools.

data.title: AI from Meta inundates child abuse investigators with excessive tips, delaying cases, as officials argue.
data.description: According to ICAC officials, the use of AI-generated reports is causing a slowdown in investigations as they are inundating investigators. Meta, however, has contested these assertions. This challenge is hindering the processing of cases as the sheer volume of AI-generated reports is overwhelming. The disagreement between ICAC officers and Meta highlights a significant issue in the investigative process. The exact number of cases affected and the extent of the slowdown caused by AI-generated reports has not been disclosed.

data.title: Block, parent company of Square, is cutting 40% of staff due to AI. CEO predicts other companies will do the same.
data.description: The parent company of Square, known as Block, is planning to reduce its workforce by 40%. CEO Jack Dorsey attributed this decision to the implementation of AI tools and forecasts that a majority of companies will also undergo similar downsizing within the next year. This move by Block has been described as part of a larger trend in which automation and technology are leading to significant job cuts across various industries.

data.title: Warner Bros. chooses Paramount's offer over Netflix, causing Netflix stock to surge.
data.description: Netflix has decided to withdraw its bid for Warner Bros. Discovery after learning that the company favored a modified offer from Paramount. Following this news, Netflix's stock experienced a significant surge overnight, indicating investor optimism. This shift in preference resulted in a positive reaction from the market, boosting Netflix's stock value.

data.title: Intuit Inc's Q2 revenue beats analyst estimates at $4.65 billion; stock slides despite adjusted earnings of $4.15/share.
data.description: Intuit Inc (NASDAQ: INTU) revealed its second-quarter fiscal 2026 financial results after the market closed on Thursday. The company reported revenue of $4.65 billion, surpassing analyst estimates of $4.53 billion. Intuit, which owns QuickBooks, Credit Karma, and TurboTax, also posted adjusted earnings of $4.15 per share for the second quarter, exceeding analyst expectations of $3.66 per share. Total revenue saw a 17% increase. Despite the positive results, INTU stock is currently experiencing a decline in value. Further details can be found on Benzinga.com.
